<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6391995>
    dc:description "Figure 9. Pharaxonotha woodruffi from Oaxaca, Mexico (A–I: male holotype; J–K: female allotype). A–C) Dorsal, lateral and ventral habitus. D–F) head, dorsal, oblique lateral and ventral views. G) Genital capsule attached to tegmen and median lobe, ventral view.H) Tegmen attached to median lobe, lateral view. I) Parameres of tegmen, ventral view top and lateral view bottom. J) Retracted ovipositor, ventral view. K) Spermatheca (fully inflated)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6391995/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

